locality: Khara Huasi, alrrededores del pueblo y tramo de 1-2 km subiendo el Río Chua Khocha. Bosque natural muy intervenido, relictos del bosque original con Juglans sp., Prestoea sp. y Alnus acuminata en las márgenes del Río.

Incachaca-Locotal. Ubicado a 5 km de la carretera, aprox. a 87 km de la ciudad de Cochabamba, bosque intervenido con presencia de cultivos de locoto.

Huayra Pata - - Major ruin discovery of large fortelezas, irrigation canals and mysterious foundations cover this ridge which is 2 km NE of the mouth of the Río Aguilani mouth at Lakachaka, and 2 km S. of the junction of the Río Mikhailpurhua and Río Aguada. 22 km N. of Choquetanga. Area of ancient ruins which has been overgrazed, burned and generally raped into semi-barren grassland with some small shrubs. Collected bordering woodlanads and mattorales
Estancia Zalazar. Laguna Zalazar. Scrub on salt flats and on border of lake and patches of dry forest.
Proposed Biosphere Reserve Gran Chaco Americano: Madrejon.
2.7 km NW of Ipatí, at highpoint on road from Ipatí to Lagunillas. Dry forest on hills, Caesalpinia paraguariensis, Capparis flexuosa, Herreria, Ximenia americana, Anadenanthera
1 km NW of Pampa Grande on dirt road to the main highway from Samaipata to Comarapa. Roadside arid scrub with cultivated fields

8 km. ESE of Comunidad Don Lorenzo. Flat, dry chaco cactus scrub forest on sandy soil, with seasonally inundated slight depressions with clay soil (curichis). Aspidosperma spp., Caesalpinia paraguariensis, Capparis retusa, Catela coccinea
Along road from La Mora to San Joaquín, 3.5 km E of La Mora and turnoff from highway from Santa Cruz to Abapó.
2.5 km on dirt road off and north from the Samaipata to Mairana highway, the turnoff just below the highest point and on the Mairana side, 7 km (by air) SE of Mairana.

Estancia San Rafael de Amboró. Ca. 30 km SE of Buena Vista along the Río Surutú. Disturbed moist tropical forest on low hills.
Apa Apa 5 km al norte de Chulumani.

Río Churu - - Following the Río Churu from 200 m W. of Aguilani to 1 km above the main fork up river. 3 km SE of the ruins of Choquecamiri, 17 km N. of Choquetanga. Riverine woodlands and mattorals, often dominated by Acalypha in the deep canyon.
Sehuencas, Proximo al pueblo de Montepunku.

Valle de Rio Zongo; 26.4 km below dam at Lago Zongo.
9.8 km NW of central plaza of Vallegrande.
On road from Mairana to Postrevalle, 12 km (by road) ESE of Quirusillas. Grazed dry woodland with Schinopsis haenkeana, Tipuana tipu, with shrubby slopes, and some clearings for cultivated fields
Parque Nacional Madidi, Moxos, Fuertecillo.

Mun. Padcaya. Cantón Emborozú. Reserva Natural Alarachi. Aguas arriba de la Quebrada Los Pinos. Sector Las Lagunitas. Bosque semideciduo estacional. Premontano Tucumano-Boliviano. Dominando Tipuana tipu, Cedrela angustifolia y Juglans australis.
Canyon of Rio Mairana, 3 km. N of highway at Yerba Buena. Dry forest and disturbed edges, bottom of valley
Parque Nacional Amboro, along Rio Isama (Rio Pitasama on topographic map). Rolling topography, sandy soil, secondary vegetation and disturbed patches of topical evergreen forest

Prov. Caballero, 3 km (by air) WSW of Comarapa, 2.9 km by road from highway at Comarapa, on gravel road to Chilón. Slopes with grazed dry thorn forest, Aspidosperma quebrachoblanco,Athyana weinmanniifolia, Gochnatia palosanto, Porlieria microphylla, Bougainvillea berberidifolia
About 0.5 km. S of and 100 m. below highest point on Mataral-El Trigal road, 3 km. NW of Estancia Cochabambita. Steep hills with dry, deciduous forest
Camino hacia la localidad de Arenales (Río Mizque).
NW of Sita, steep slopes facing Inquisivi. Disturbed forest slopes with Alnus.
Madidi, Cerranias de los alrededores de San Buenaventura.

Parque Nacional Madidi, rio Tuichi, arroyo Pintata. Bosque andino semideciduo chaparro con Tabebuia aurea, Astronium urundeuva, Anadenanthera colubrina, Trichilia elegans, Jacaranda cuspidifolia. Plantas secadas en campo.
Santo Domingo, Trayecto entre el pueblo y campamento arroyo Tintaya. Bosques secundarios de yungas subandino superior pluvial dominados por Guadua sp., en partes chacras. En terraza plana.
Huascañada.

Canton Iguembe. Bosque de transicion entre chaco serrano y Bosque chaqueno, dominado por Enterolobium contortisiliquum en los bosques con doseles altos y Acacias ssp. en bosques mas abiertos. Colectada a media ladera adyacente al rio.

Parque Nacional Amboró. San Juan del Potrero al norte 25 Km. Bosque nublado estacionalmente seco con Podocarpus rusbyi, Prumnopitys exigua, Myrcianthes sp, Blepharocalyx salicifolius, Dicksonia yellouiana, Crinodendron tucumanum.
Parque Nacional Noel Kempff Mercado. Lago Caimán. Farrallon arriba del campamento, afloramiento de arenisca.
Parque Nacional Defensores del Chaco: Madrejón Area. Dry forest and swamps; sandy soil.
Parque Nacional Madidi, NW de Apolo, senda Azariamas - San Fermín.
Area Natural de Manejo Integrado Apolobamba, Carpa. Bosque montano estacional con Myrtaceae sp. y Nectandra spp. Inventario fitosociologico Madidi 35. Plantas sin alcoholizar.

Gorge of Río Bermejo, along highway from Samaipata to Santa Cruz, 1.5 km E of Río Las Cruces (Río Vicoquín) bridge, 5.5 km (by road) WSW of Bermejo. Dry forest on steep rocky slope, with Schinopsis haenkeana, Anadenanthera macrocarpa, Acacia polyphylla, Piptadenia buchtienii, Muntingia calabura
Bella Vista, camino del Refugio hacia las Lajas, sobre el camino principal.
2 km. N of center of Concepcion. Forest and edge of savanna on slope and along small creek
Proposed Biosphere Reserve Gran Chaco Americano: Cerro León. Seasonal forests on clay soils.
Río Blanco, 3 km al W de Campo Quijano, vías del FF.CC entre los puentes de los ríos Blanco y Toro o Rosario

5 km S of Cotoca and 1 km W of road from Cotoca to Paurito. Brushy roadside and fields with mostly weedy species, flat, fine-sandy soil, mostly cultivated fields, with a few Acrocomia totai, much Tecoma stans

Parque Nacional Madidi, rio Tuichi, Virgen del Rosario. Bosque andino semideciduo con Anadenanthera colubrina y Trichilia elegans; vegetacion ribereña con Cecropia spp., Gynerium sagittatum. Plantas secadas en campo.
10 km by gravel road SE of San José and the turnoff from the Santa Cruz-Samaipata highway.
E and NE sides of Camiri, sandy, disturbed areas, dry deciduous thorn scrub, along Río Parapeti
Bajando hacia el puente santa rosa.
Reserva Ecológica El Refugio, a 300 m del campamento refugio hacia el campamento Toledo sobre el Río Paraguá. En un cordon con bosque pionero. Suelos arcillo-limosos con arena fina y humus.

9 km. SE of Comarapa on highway to San Isidro. Grazed arid scrub along Quebrada Pujio, a dry wash. Achatocarpus, Prosopis alba, P. kuntzei, Capparis atamisquea, C. speciosa, Acacia aroma, Harrisia tephracantha

Estación Experimental Valle de Sacta de la Universidad San Simon, media camino CBBA-S.C. (El Chapare). Bosque primario, muy húmedo, con Tapirira guianensis, Eschweilera sp., Iriartea deltoides & Jessenia sp. Curso Dendrologica del USAID & PL-480.

Parque Nacional Kaa-Iya del Gran Chaco, ANMI Norte. 58 km al O del campamento San José, sobre el gasoducto. Bosques chaqueños pluviestacionales mal drenados (Diplokeleba-Trithrinax) y medianamente drenados (Diplokeleba-Phyllostylon), en su limite con los xéricos.

E side of Rio Yapacani at junction with Rio Surutu, 0.5 km. upstream and S from highway bridge over Rio Yapacani at Villa Yapacani. Disturbed shrubby areas, soil sandy, Rhamnidium elaeocarpum, Cestrum strigillatum
Bajando de Azurduy hacia el río Pilcomayo.
Siberia. Sobre la carretera se encuentra la laguna Movible. Se caracteriza por ser un bosque nublado con mucha abundancia de Ericaceae y Melastomataceae, generalmente intervenido por la ganaderia.
Estancia Thacra; a 4 km al este sobre Río Comarapa.

Parque Nacional Noel Kempff Mercado. Campamento Las Torres. Bosque seco con afloramiento rocoso. Ladera del bosque con abundante Bromelia en estrato herbáceo y abundante bambú. Parcela permanente de estudio.

3 km W of Puerto Pailas, along dirt road to Santa Cruz and railroad. Flat, disturbed scrubby Chaco vegetation; soil fine sand and clay. With Acacia albocorticata, Acrocomia totai, Caesalpinia pluviosa, Trichilia stellato-tomentosa, Capparis retusa, C. prisca
Along Río Ichilo, 2.1 km by dirt road S from turnoff from main Buena Vista-Villa Tunari highway. Edge of floodplain, a narrow strip of secondary trees, but mostly in banana plantations
Alrededor de Tumi Chucua. Bosque secundario, arbustivo

Cerro Pelado - - Along the road between Marimonos and Quiquibey in the area of Cerro Pelado. ca. 20 km NE of Palos Blancos. Grassy and shrubby slopes on upper ridges. Somewhat similar habitat to that found near the summit of Amboró.
5 km S of Mataral on road to Vallegrande. Arid cactus scrub on gentle slopes of valley bottom, Capparis speciosa, Prosopis kuntzei, Vallesia glabra, Vassobia breviflora
Miguillas-Cumbre Miguillas - - Along the road between Miguillas and the cumbre between the Río Miguillas and the Río La Paz. Deciduous forests.
1.2 km WNW of the Santa Cruz-Samaipata highway in San José, along floodplain of Río Piraí.

Prov. Santiesteban, 3 km E of San José. Flat area of clay loam, originally subtropical semi-deciduous or evergreen forest with much Attalea phalerata, Ficus, Hura crepitans, Crateva tapia, now mostly cleared for sugarcane and other field crops

6 km NW of turnoff from highway at Río Seco on dirt road toward La Florida. Chaco forest on slightly rolling area, sandy soil. With Astronium, Anadenanthera macrocarpa, Phyllostylon rhamnoides, Bromelia serra, Capparis speciosa, C. retusa, Ximenia americana, Acanthosyris falcata, Achatocarpus praecox

50 km al norte de Mataral (en la carretera Santa Cruz-Comarapa) pasando por San Juan del Potrero y bajando a la cuenca del alto Río Ichilo. Bosque pluvial montano, estado primario, en fondo del valle. Especimenes preservados en alcohol.
